  "text": "Given the currents on the radiating elements, calculating the radiation pattern and plotting it to visualize it is one of the tasks of antenna analysis. In this section, we will show how a built-in function of the signal processing toolbox is used in antenna analysis. The array factor of n isotropic point sources with different excitations placed along the x axis on the x-y plane is given by [CITATION_1] AF = w 0 + w 1 e jψ + w 2 e j2ψ + . . . + w n−1 e j(n−1)ψ",
